column4: Fix some bugs of AI and delete useless code

Fixes issues with the selected endpoint handling.  Endpoint instances now keep a reference to the selected endpoint object  instead of holding the selecting endpoint ID.  Holding the selected endpoint ID could lead to problems if  for example  the endpoint expired and another endpoint with the same endpoint ID joined the conference.

fixing room name  When you have an Apache server and you are getting an url with a trailing "/" (ex: '/meeting/') you could have troubles with the room name. Without this patch the room name may be "meeting/@your.own.server" and this could lead problems with your XMPP server

Merge pull request #2 from jitsi/master  fixing room name When you have an HTTPD server and you are getting an url with a trailing "/" (ex: '/meeting/') you could have troubles with the room name if you're using specific rooms on fixed URLs. Without this patch the room name may be "meeting/@your.own.server" and this could lead problems with your XMPP server

Fixing room name  When you have an HTTPD server and you are getting an url with a trailing "/" (ex: '/meeting/') you could have troubles with the room name if you're using specific rooms on fixed URLs. Without this patch the room name may be "meeting/@your.own.server" and this could lead problems with your XMPP server

Fix stream end/start race condition  We need to queue attempts to call modifySources to prevent errors in setLocalDescription  et al. We need to let the asynchronous function flow in modifySources finish before we kick off another set.

Fix stream end/start race condition  We need to queue attempts to call modifySources to prevent errors in setLocalDescription  et al. We need to let the asynchronous function flow in modifySources finish before we kick off another set.

Always uplifts RTP timestamps upon rewriting.  This commit attempts to fix the (now very rare) scrambling video problem that we have been observing in our deployments. In particular  there's no reason to enforce a threshold for the RTP timestamp uplifting. If packets with old timestamps reach a receiver's jitter buffer they can break the decoding process.

fix(JingleSessionPC): send SSRC updates regardless of the ICE state  ICE connectivity issues can be transient and those should not prevent from sending SSRC updates. XMPP stream is a separate connection/stream and skipping the updates while ICE is disconnected results in broken media session where the stream information is not propagated correctly across the conference participants.

fix: set a default color for text in modal dialogs  Some atlaskit components  such as field-text  inherit text color. This is a problem with components that are white as they will inherit $defaultColor  which is a light gray. So instead  for the atlaskit modal  set a color for all the form content so it can be inherited instead.

Openfire plugin should expose its Component  This is a fix for https://github.com/jitsi/jitsi-videobridge/issues/338 which is an issue similar to https://github.com/jitsi/jitsi-videobridge/issues/335. Fix OverconstrainedError handling in Firefox  Firefox uses "constraint" as the key in the error:  ``` [modules/RTC/RTCUtils.js] <value/<>:  Failed to get access to local media. Error MediaStreamError { name: "OverconstrainedError"  message: "Constraints could be not satisfied."  constraint: "width"  stack: "" } Object { audio: false  video: Object }  lib-jitsi-meet.min.js:6:10419 ```
fix(ParticipantConn...Status): bug in p2p status  When video track is frozen in P2P mode it should be INTERRUPTED instead of INACTIVE.

fix(vertical-filmstrip): prevent scaling based on video count  Vertical filmstrip has a scrollbar to scroll through all remote videos instead of scaling width and height to force all remote videos to display on screen. Update XmppProtocolProvider.java  The focus user connects with SASL Mechanisms ANONYMOUS or PLAIN  but might try to authenticate  with a non supported mechanism if one is offered by the server.  This moves the preference of PLAIN to the top  and disables the unused mechanisms.  This should resolve issue #203 https://github.com/jitsi/jicofo/issues/203

Fix a bug regarding messageID's and interim results  We closed a session when Google send an END_OF_SINGLE_UTTERANCE event  which was received before the final result came in. This resulted in the JSON object with the final result getting a new message ID.  This commit fixed this issue by making a new ResponseObserver for each session  where each ResponseObserver has its own unique ID
